team1 = [[Qatar national under-20 football team|Qatar U20]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 4\n| nationalgoals1 = 4\n| nationalyears2 = 2007\u20132013\n| nationalteam2 = [[Qatar national under-23 football team|Qatar U23]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 14\n| nationalgoals2 = 6\n| nationalyears3 = 2008\u2013\n| nationalteam3 = [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 131\n| nationalgoals3 = 27\n| club-update = 31 December 2015\n| nationalteam-update = 19:56, 5 December 2019 (UTC)\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{fb|QAT}}}}\n{{MedalSport|Men's [[Association football|Football]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[AFC Asian Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|Winner|[[2019 AFC Asian Cup|2019 UAE]]|[[Qatar national football team|Team]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Hassan Khalid al-Haydos''' ({{lang-ar|\u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u064a\u062f\u0648\u0633}}; born 11 December 1990) is a Qatari [[football (soccer)|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Al-Sadd Sports Club|Al Sadd]], in addition to playing for the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].\n\n==Club career==\n[[File:Hassan Al Haidous 2012 1.jpg|thumb|Al-Haydos playing for Al Sadd in a [[Qatar Stars League|Stars League]] match in 2012]]\nHaidous started playing football for [[Al-Sadd Sports Club|Al Sadd]] at the age of eight, advancing through the ranks until he reached the first team at age seventeen. He had support and guidance early on from [[Jafal Rashed Al-Kuwari]].<ref>[http://www.alarab.com.qa/details.php?docId=74297&issueNo=431&secId=20 \u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u064a\u062f\u0648\u0633: \u0646\u062c\u0627\u062d\u0627\u062a \u062c\u0641\u0627\u0644 \u0644\u0646 \u062a\u062a\u0648\u0642\u0641 \u0639\u0646\u062f \u062a\u0631\u0643\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0639\u0628] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20120717033804/http://www.alarab.com.qa/details.php?docId=74297&issueNo=431&secId=20 |date=2012-07-17 }} {{in lang|ar}}</ref>\n\nHe was one of the players to take a penalty kick in the penalty-shootout against [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors|Jeonbuk]] in the [[2011 AFC Champions League]], scoring after the ball reflected off the top post. The victory ensured Al Sadd would earn a place in the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] as the representative for Asia. In the third-place match between Al Sadd and [[Kashiwa Reysol]], he was again selected to take one of the penalty kicks after the match had ended 0\u20130. The penalty shoot-out was won by Al Sadd 5\u20133.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120913214829/http://www.qfa.com.qa/al-sadd-beat-kashiwa-reysol-for-third-place-in-club-world-cup--.aspx QFA - Al Sadd beat Kashiwa Reysol for third place in Club World Cup]</ref>\n\nHe was voted as the 'Best Qatari Player' in 2014 in a poll conducted by Doha Stadium, receiving 58 out of 104 votes from a panel of analysts, coaches and administrators.<ref name=\"alkass1\">{{cite web|url=http://cdn.alkass.net/news_details.aspx?news_id=81901|title=\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u062f \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0648\u062d\u0629: \u0627\u0644\u0647\u064a\u062f\u0648\u0633 \u0623\u0641\u0636\u0644 \u0644\u0627\u0639\u0628 \u0641\u064a 2014|publisher=alkass.net|date=5 January 2015|accessdate=5 January 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150106030410/http://cdn.alkass.net/news_details.aspx?news_id=81901|archive-date=6 January 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAl-Haydos made his debut for the [[Qatar national under-23 football team|Qatar Olympic team]] in 2007, coming off the bench to score a late goal against [[Japan national under-23 football team|Japan]] in the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Asian Qualifiers Preliminary Round 3|2008 Summer Olympic Qualifiers]] in order to help his team salvage a 2\u20131 win.<ref>[http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/2339.pdf AFC - Qatar U-23 vs Japan U-23 - Match Summary]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He featured in two other matches in the competition, one against Saudi Arabia,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/2341.pdf |title=AFC - Qatar U-23 vs Saudi Arabia U-23 - Match Summary |access-date=2012-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120614220314/http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/2341.pdf |archive-date=2012-06-14 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and one against Vietnam, where he scored a goal;<ref>[http://images.the-afc.com/Documents/competitions/fixtures/2343.pdf AFC - Qatar U-23 vs Saudi Arabia U-23 - Match Summary]{{Dead link|date=July 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> both as second-half substitutes. He also played a large part in the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's Asian Qualifiers|2012 Summer Olympic Qualifiers]] as the captain, scoring a goal against India in the preliminary stage.<ref>[https://archive.is/20120913234000/http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/joomleague/?view=report&compID=407&matchId=3897 AFC - Qatar U-23 vs India U-23 - Match Summary]</ref> He played all the matches in the group stage, scoring a goal against Oman,<ref>[http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/joomleague/?view=report&compID=407&matchId=4173 AFC - Qatar U-23 vs Oman U-23 - Match Summary]</ref> and scoring against Saudi Arabia after being set up by [[Saleh Bader Al Yazidi|Saleh Badr]] to give Qatar a 2\u20131 win and a glimpse of hope for qualifying for the Olympics.<ref>[http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/joomleague/?view=report&compID=407&matchId=4170 AFC - Qatar U-23 vs Saudi Arabia U-23 - Match Summary]</ref> He won the [[Man of the Match]] award.<ref>[http://cdn.alkass.net/news_details.aspx?news_id=32709 \u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u064a\u062f\u0648\u0633 : \u0647\u062f\u0641\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0623\u0647\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u0649 \u0627\u0648\u0644\u0645\u0628\u064a\u0627\u062f \u0644\u0646\u062f\u0646] {{in lang|ar}}</ref>\n\nHaidous has made several appearances for the senior [[Qatar national football team]], including a [[2010 FIFA World Cup]] qualifying match against Bahrain on 10 September 2008.<ref>{{FIFA player|284190|Hasan Al Haydos}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.allsoccerplayers.com/en/associations/cteam-153.html?PHPSESSID=ba5d4fa50c3836ee846cd4aa4571b680 |title=Qatar National Team |work=All Soccer Players |accessdate=2008-12-07 }}{{dead link|date=October 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n===International matches===\n<!-- NOTE: when updating stats, update the infobox too! -->\n{{updated|5 December 2019}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/qat-haydos-intlg.html |title=Hassan Khalid Al-Haydos - Century of International Appearances |author=Husain Mohammed |publisher=RSSSF |date=21 August 2019 }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2008||5||0\n|-\n|2009||10||0\n|-\n|2010||4||0\n|-\n|2011||3||0\n|-\n|2012||6||0\n|-\n|2013||18||1\n|-\n|2014||12||2\n|-\n|2015||13||6\n|-\n|2016||11||5\n|-\n|2017||17||6\n|-\n|2018||12||4\n|-\n|2019||20||3\n|-\n!Total!!131!!27\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Qatar's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\">{{cite web|url=http://www.national-football-teams.com/player/27516/Hassan_Khalid_Al_Haydos.html|title=Al-Haydos, Hassan Khalid|website=National Football Teams|accessdate=14 June 2017}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|- style=\"background:#8fcfdf;\"\n| \u2014 || 30 December 2008 || [[Thani bin Jassim Stadium]], [[Al Rayyan]] || {{fb|LBY|1977}} || align=\"center\"| '''3'''\u20131 || align=\"center\"| 5\u20132 || Unofficial friendly\n|-\n| 1. || 13 October 2013  || Thani bin Jassim Stadium, Al Rayyan || {{fb|YEM}} || align=\"center\"| '''2'''\u20130 || align=\"center\"| 6\u20130 || [[2015 AFC Asian Cup qualification]]\n|-\n| 2. || 6 October 